HEADWORD: Quinible
<hw>Quin"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>quini</ets> five each.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An interval of
a fifth; also, a part sung with such intervals.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧He sang . . . a loud
<xex>quynyble</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

